How to Open and Operate a .ipynb (Jupyter Notebook) File (Step-by-Step)

Install VS Code (if not installed).
Install Jupyter Extension
Open VS Code, go to Extensions (Ctrl+Shift+X), and search for Jupyter → Install it.
Open the .ipynb File in VS Code
Drag and drop your .ipynb file into VS Code or open it via File → Open File.
Run the cells using the "Run" button or Shift + Enter.


Open in a Web Browser

Save the Files:
Save your HTML file as index.html
Save your CSS file as style.css (if using an external stylesheet).

Link CSS to HTML:
Inside the <head> section of your HTML file, add:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

Double Click to Open:
Locate the HTML file in your folder.
Double-click it – It will open in your default web browser.
